- @title = "About"

#about.static_page
  %p
    %h3 About
    Redactify is a twitter front-end for a user's timeline with tweets with specified tags redacted as to not spoil events that
    a user might not be able to watch in real time.

  %p
    %h3 Redactify is written and maintained by
    %ul
      %li= auto_link("Dan McNevin - dpmcnevin@redactify.com")
      

  %p 
    %h3 Redactify is open source
    %ul
      %li= link_to "Redactify GitHub repository", "http://github.com/dpmcnevin/redactify"
      %li= link_to "Fork of twitter-auth", "http://github.com/dpmcnevin/twitter-auth"

  %p
    %h3 Follow us on Twitter
    %ul
      %li= "#{auto_link_twitter("@redactify")} - System updates and status".html_safe
      %li= "#{auto_link_twitter("@mental_thinking")} - Dan McNevin".html_safe

  %p
    %h3 Acknowledgments
    %ul
      %li= link_to "Twitter", "http://twitter.com"
      %li= link_to "Ruby on Rails", "http://rubyonrails.com"
      %li= link_to "Heroku", "http://heroku.com"
      %li= "Michael Bleigh's #{link_to "twitter_auth", "http://github.com/mbleigh/twitter-auth"} gem.".html_safe